<!--
==========================================================================
HOW TO: WRITING IMMERSIVE FRIENDLY PDA CONVERSATIONS
==========================================================================

P.A.N.D.A. is a modular simulation framework for S.T.A.L.K.E.R. Anomaly that
turns every PDA conversation into a real gameplay event. Nothing is cosmetic.
If an NPC says "bandits are closing in", bandits actually spawn. If they say
"I left supplies at a stash (our system doesnt know where a stash is going to be spawned at till it spawns)", a real location marker appears on the
player's PDA map and a real stash or item reward triggers when they arrive.
Every word in a conversation must be backed by a trackable mechanic.

The goal: 100% simulated conversations that affect real gameplay and create
interesting situations using real game state in real time.

==========================================================================
PART 1 — WHAT THE SYSTEM CAN TRACK & SIMULATE
==========================================================================

The engine reads the following live game state at conversation time:

  PLAYER STATE (available as placeholders in dialogue text):
  - $player_name          Actor's name
  - $npc_name             Conversation NPC's name
  - $player_faction       Player's faction (translated)
  - $npc_faction          NPC's faction (translated)
  - $current_level        Current map name (translated)
  - $player_money         Roubles on hand
  - $player_rank          Rank title (novice -> legend)
  - $player_reputation    Numeric reputation value
  - $companion_count      Number of active companions
  - $time_of_day          "morning" / "afternoon" / "evening" / "night"
  - $game_hour            Current time as "HH:MM"

  SMART TERRAIN LEVEL PLACEHOLDERS (random location per level):
  Use %<level_key>_panda_st% anywhere in dialogue text.
  The system picks a random field smart terrain from that level and
  substitutes the translated vanilla name at runtime. The same location
  is used consistently across all turns of one conversation.

	 %garbage_panda_st% = picks a random from list of garbage smart terrains [st_gar_smart_terrain_3_7_name] = "Garbage. Vehicle Graveyard"
	so dialogues dont need to specify anything about locations and just let the engine handle the id/text swap. 
	
	Example: 
	
	" Was waslking near %garbage_panda_st% and i think i saw a squad of Mercs, maybe waiting to ambush someone?"
	 
  Available level keys:
    %cordon_panda_st%        %darkscape_panda_st%     %swamp_panda_st%
    %garbage_panda_st%       %agroprom_panda_st%      %dark_valley_panda_st%
    %yantar_panda_st%        %wild_territory_panda_st% %rostok_panda_st%
    %truck_cemetery_panda_st% %dead_city_panda_st%     %army_warehouses_panda_st%
    %radar_panda_st%         %red_forest_panda_st%    %limansk_panda_st%
    %pripyat_panda_st%       %generators_panda_st%    %outskirts_panda_st%
    %jupiter_panda_st%       %south_cnpp_panda_st%    %north_cnpp_panda_st%
    %zaton_panda_st%         %meadow_panda_st%

  These exclude safezones, faction HQs and NPC hubs (Rookie Village,
  100 Rads Bar, Yanov Station, Skadovsk, Freedom/Duty bases, etc.) so
  conversations always reference potential dangerous field locations.

  Example text usage:
    "I spotted movement near %cordon_panda_st%, be careful if you head that way."

  PRECONDITIONS (checked before conversation fires):
  The system can gate conversations on any combination of:
  - Money:         req_money:<amount>, req_money_max:<amount>
  - Rank:          req_rank:<rank>, req_rank_max:<rank>
  - Reputation:    req_rep:<amount>, req_rep_max:<amount>
  - Kills:         req_kills:<count>, req_mutant_kills:<count>
  - Faction:       req_faction:<fac>, req_not_faction:<fac>
  - NPC faction:   req_npc_faction:<fac>, req_npc_not_faction:<fac>
  - Location:      req_level:<map>, req_not_level:<map>
  - Companions:    req_companions:<n>, req_companions_max:<n>
  - Goodwill:      req_goodwill:<amount>:<fac>, req_goodwill_max:<amount>:<fac>
  - Inventory:     req_has_item:<section>
  - Equipment:     req_equipped:<section>, req_equipped_slot:<slot>
  - Achievements:  req_achievement:<id>
  - Time of day:   req_time_day, req_time_night
  - Health:        req_health_min:<0..1>, req_health_max:<0..1>
  - NPC rank:      req_npc_rank:<rank>, req_npc_rank_max:<rank>

  Ranks (ascending): novice, trainee, experienced, professional,
                     veteran, expert, master, legend.

  OUTCOMES (real gameplay effects executed after NPC reply):
  - reward_money:<amount>                     Give roubles
  - punish_money:<amount>                     Deduct roubles
  - reward_rep:<amount>                       Increase reputation
  - punish_rep:<amount>                       Decrease reputation
  - reward_gw:<amount>:<faction>              Improve faction goodwill
  - punish_gw:<amount>:<faction>              Decrease faction goodwill
  - give_item:<section>                       Spawn item in player inventory
  - courier_item:<section>                    Send courier NPC with item
  - reward_stash  (it spawns a random stash ramdonly around the world by vanilla systems outside our control) Marks a random stash
  - spawn_companion:<faction>[:delay_s]       Spawn friendly squad nearby
  - spawn_hostile:<faction>[:delay_s]         Spawn hostile squad nearby
  - spawn_mutant:<type|random>[:delay_s]      Spawn mutant pack nearby
  - watch_location:<st_key>[:radius]          Mark location on PDA map
  - watch_location_trigger:<st_key>:<cmd>[:radius]  Mark + trigger on arrival
  - teleport_npc_to_smart:<st_key>[:delay_s]  Move NPC to smart terrain
  - teleport_npc_to_player[:delay_s]          Move NPC near player
  - recruit_companion[:no_dismiss]            Recruit NPC as companion
  - chance:<percent>:<command>                Probability wrapper

  Spawn types for spawn_mutant:
    dog, pseudodog, cat, boar, snork, bloodsucker, lurker, chimera,
    controller, burer, fracture, psysucker, random

==========================================================================
PART 2 — CONVERSATION STRUCTURE & FORMAT
==========================================================================

  1) ID FORMAT
  Base key:  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_<field>
  Turn key:  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_<id>_t<turn>_<field>

  2) REQUIRED FIELDS PER CONVERSATION
  For turn 1 (the opener):
    _open               NPC's opening message
    _precond            Comma-separated preconditions (optional but recommended)
    _choice_1 .. _choice_4   Player response options (stop at first missing)
    _reply_1  .. _reply_4    NPC reply to each choice
    _outcome_1 .. _outcome_4 Gameplay effects per choice (or "none")
    _cont_1   .. _cont_4     Next turn number (2, 3, 4...) or 0/absent = end
    _timeout             Seconds before conversation expires (real-time)
    _timeout_msg         NPC's annoyed closeout if player ignores

  For turn 2+:
    _t2_choice_1, _t2_reply_1, _t2_outcome_1, _t2_cont_1
    _t3_choice_1, _t3_reply_1, _t3_outcome_1, _t3_cont_1
    etc.

  3) SELECTION FLOW
    a) Script determines friendly vs hostile pool based on NPC relation.
    b) Iterates all conversations, evaluating preconditions against the
       specific NPC and current game state.
    c) Eligible conversations enter weighted random selection with
       cooldown penalties to prevent repetition.
    d) Per-NPC cooldown prevents the same stalker messaging twice in
       quick succession.

==========================================================================
PART 3 — HOW TO WRITE REALISTIC IMMERSIVE CONVERSATIONS
==========================================================================

  RULE 1: EVERYTHING MUST BE REAL
  If the NPC claims something is happening, the outcome must simulate it.
  "Bandits nearby" -> spawn_hostile:bandit.  "Found a stash" -> reward_stash.
  "I owe you" -> reward_money. Never write dialogue that promises something
  without a matching outcome. The player will SEE the result in-game.

  RULE 2: USE PRECONDITIONS TO SET THE STAGE
  Don't write a conversation about "your team" if the player has no companions.
  Don't reference nighttime danger during the day. Use preconditions to ensure
  conversations only trigger when the context makes sense:
    - Night ambush scenario:  req_time_night
    - Wealthy trader talk:    req_money:10000
    - Veteran-to-veteran:     req_rank:veteran,req_npc_rank:veteran
    - Zone-specific events:   req_level:l03_agroprom

  The more specific the preconditions, the more immersive the result. Players
  will only see conversations that match their exact situation.

  RULE 3: BRANCHES = REAL CHOICES WITH REAL CONSEQUENCES
  Each branch should represent a distinct player stance that varies by conversation:
   Example:
    - Cooperative:  Help the NPC -> rewards, reputation, allies
    - Cautious:     Ask questions, gather info -> moderate outcomes
    - Greedy:       Demand payment -> money but reputation/goodwill cost
    - Dismissive:   Refuse -> minor penalties, possibly missed opportunities

  Every choice should have a tangible result. No "fluff" branches that do
  nothing. Even declining should have consequences (goodwill loss, missed
  stash info, etc.).

  RULE 4: PDA TONE ONLY
  All dialogue is remote PDA text communication. Write like someone texting
  over a PDA :
    - Short, practical sentences
    - Signal/battery concerns
    - Urgency appropriate to the Zone
    - No face-to-face narration or stage directions

  RULE 5: LOCATION REFERENCES MUST BE ACTIONABLE
  When mentioning a location, use %level_panda_st% for the text AND pair it
  with watch_location or watch_location_trigger in the outcome. This places
  a real marker on the player's PDA map. When they arrive, the system
  acknowledges it and can trigger additional effects (spawns, rewards, etc.).

  RULE 6: MULTI-TURN DEPTH
  Use the _cont_X field to create branching conversation trees. A cautious
  "tell me more" response on turn 1 leads to turn 2 with new information
  and new choices. This creates natural conversation flow where the player
  builds trust or suspicion over multiple exchanges. Each turn should
  escalate or evolve the situation, not just repeat the same stakes.

  RULE 7: MATCH THE ZONE
  S.T.A.L.K.E.R. is harsh, unpredictable, and morally grey. Conversations
  should reflect this:
    - NPCs might be lying or exaggerating for personal gain
    - Rewards might come with hidden dangers (chance:40:spawn_hostile)
    - Helping someone might anger another faction (punish_gw)
    - The Zone itself is a threat (spawn_mutant as environmental pressure)
    - Nothing is free; everything has a cost

  RULE 8: USE CHANCE FOR UNCERTAINTY
  The Zone is unpredictable. Use chance:<percent>:<command> to create
  situations where outcomes aren't guaranteed within reason:
    - chance:60:reward_stash       (stash info might be outdated)
    - chance:30:spawn_hostile:bandit:90  (bandits might show up)
    - chance:50:spawn_mutant:random:120  (mutant activity reported but unconfirmed)
  This creates emergent gameplay where players can't predict exact results.

==========================================================================
PART 4 — QUICK TEMPLATE
==========================================================================

  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_precond        req_time_day,req_rank:experienced
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_open           NPC opener text with $placeholders
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_choice_1       Cooperative response
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_reply_1        NPC reply
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_outcome_1      reward_money:2000,reward_gw:5:stalker
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_cont_1         2  (continue to turn 2)
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_choice_2       Cautious response
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_reply_2        NPC reply
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_outcome_2      none
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_cont_2         2
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_choice_3       Greedy response
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_reply_3        NPC reply
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_outcome_3      reward_money:5000,punish_gw:10:stalker
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_cont_3         0  (conversation ends)
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_choice_4       Dismissive response
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_reply_4        NPC reply
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_outcome_4      punish_gw:5:stalker
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_cont_4         0
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_timeout        90
  st_pda_ic_friendly_loner_99_timeout_msg    "Guess you're busy. Out."

